description.narrative: Output 1.2 More children, adolescents and women benefit from improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal, new-born, child, and adolescent health interventions, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more vulnerable neonates, infants and children survive and thrive and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth
